---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="About | MX+C" description="Who we are and how to contact MX+C.">
  <article class="page">
    <h1>About MX+C</h1>
    <p>
      MX+C exists to close the gap between ambitious AI ideas and dependable production software.
      We combine deep technical reasoning with pragmatic delivery so teams can ship with confidence.
    </p>
  </article>

  <section class="section section-tight">
    <div class="section-head">
      <p class="eyebrow">Our approach</p>
      <h2>Pragmatic by default</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="grid">
      <article class="card">
        <h3>Outcome-led scoping</h3>
        <p>We define measurable outcomes first, then choose the smallest technical path that can achieve them.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="card">
        <h3>Visible tradeoffs</h3>
        <p>We document risks and decisions as we go, so there are no hidden surprises late in delivery.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="card">
        <h3>Maintainable handover</h3>
        <p>You get clean, operable systems with enough context for your team to continue confidently.</p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <article class="page" id="contact">
    <h2 id="how-we-work">How we work</h2>
    <p>
      Engagements are usually short and focused. Typical shape: discovery + prototype + production-hardening.
      We work in weekly cycles with direct communication and explicit checkpoints.
    </p>

    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <p><strong>Post:</strong> MX+C Ltd c/o WG LS17 9FD</p>
    <p><strong>Email:</strong> <a href="mailto:contact@mxpc.io">contact@mxpc.io</a></p>
    <p><strong>GitHub:</strong> <a href="https://github.com/mxpc" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">github.com/mxpc</a></p>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
